<p>Something came up today that I did not know, so I’m sharing the rule here. Our club runs under the Open+ chart. Even on that chart there are restrictions on what you need to open 2c. Under the Open+ chart, you must be both within a trick of game and have at least 5 A/K control points for a 2c opening to be legal. The hand in question tonight was KQJxxx  KQJxxxx void void. If it’s a 2c opener for your partnership, you must alert your 2c openers, as I understand the rule.</p>

